      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09A\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Copy decision table into table J09A_temp where the tour starts with J09A.\\n2. Add ENTSCHEIDUNG column.\\n3. Classify meter reading type. Apply rules: 1. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"KSA\\\" when a HAUS has less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\". 2. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \\\"EVU\\\".\\n4. JOIN table with EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\\n5. JOIN table with SALES_MASTER and NET_MASTER. Join table with NET_MASTER and SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR.\\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\\n7. If \\\"sales customer data NOT empty\\\":\\n    8. Use sales customer data table entries.\\n   Else:\\n    9. Use net data customer table entries.\\n10. Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09A. Use this column names, when exporting the file: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n11. Send email with the CSV file to EVU. Email address meter.readings@evu.com, file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>.\\n12. Delete temporary table.\"}",
            "id": "lc_c7196f01-faaf-49c7-a346-077741f70408"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "e2c133da-1c64-4980-9eb7-8706b83924b5",
        "tool_call_id": "call_2uyb91zw",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09A",
            "process_rule": "1. Copy decision table into table J09A_temp where the tour starts with J09A.\n2. Add ENTSCHEIDUNG column.\n3. Classify meter reading type. Apply rules: 1. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"KSA\" when a HAUS has less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\". 2. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \"EVU\".\n4. JOIN table with EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\n5. JOIN table with SALES_MASTER and NET_MASTER. Join table with NET_MASTER and SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR.\n6. Compare customer sales master data and net master data.\n7. If \"sales customer data NOT empty\":\n    8. Use sales customer data table entries.\n   Else:\n    9. Use net data customer table entries.\n10. Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09A. Use this column names, when exporting the file: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n11. Send email with the CSV file to EVU. Email address meter.readings@evu.com, file_path: <path_to_exported_csv_file>.\n12. Delete temporary table."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
